{"questionId":"12181","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{a}{b} = {\\text{tan}}\\,\\theta \">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>a</mi>\n    <mi>b</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong> EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>use of a right triangle, leading to the required result. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>Use of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\,\\theta&nbsp; = \\frac{{{\\text{sin}}\\,\\theta }}{{{\\text{cos}}\\,\\theta }}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>θ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cos</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>θ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;leading to the required result. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12181","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.5f.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that a b = tan θ .","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"f.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.7—Circular functions: graphs, composites, transformations","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Compound angle identities"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}